<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62c5f940-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3745"><num value="3745">§ 3745.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c5f941-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3745/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> General authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary to carry out the purposes of this chapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id62c5f942-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s3745/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Funding source</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The activities required under subchapter II may only be funded from appropriations made pursuant to this chapter. To the greatest extent possible, such activities shall be coordinated with activities funded from other sources.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id62c5f943-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/177/tIII/s305">Pub. L. 103–177, title III, § 305</ref>, <date date="1993-12-03">Dec. 3, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/2023">107 Stat. 2023</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
